# Package Creation Plan: @megacampus/claude-agents

## Goal
Create NPM package for easy deployment of Claude Code agent ecosystem to new projects.

## Package Info
- **Name**: `create-claude-agents` (or `@megacampus/create-claude-agents`)
- **Version**: 1.0.0
- **Type**: CLI tool (npx compatible)
- **Registry**: npm (public or private)

## Installation Method

```bash
# New project
npx create-claude-agents

# Existing project
npx create-claude-agents --merge
```

## Package Structure

```
create-claude-agents/
├── package.json              # Package metadata
├── README.md                 # Installation guide
├── LICENSE                   # MIT
├── bin/
│   └── cli.js               # Main CLI script
├── templates/
│   ├── .claude/
│   │   ├── agents/          # All 32 agents
│   │   ├── commands/        # Slash commands
│   │   └── skills/          # 14 skills
│   ├── docs/
│   │   └── Agents Ecosystem/ # 4 docs
│   ├── .mcp.json            # Minimal MCP config
│   ├── .mcp.full.json       # Extended MCP config
│   └── CLAUDE.md            # Project conventions
└── scripts/
    └── postinstall.js       # Setup automation

Total size: ~200KB (32 agents + 14 skills + 4 docs)
```

## CLI Features

### Interactive Setup
```bash
npx create-claude-agents
? Project name: my-project
? Install location: ./
? MCP config: minimal/full/both
? Include docs: yes/no
✓ Copying agents...
✓ Setting up MCP...
✓ Creating CLAUDE.md...
✓ Done! Run /health-bugs to test
```

### Options
```bash
--dir <path>          # Target directory (default: ./)
--mcp minimal|full    # MCP config (default: minimal)
--skip-docs          # Skip documentation
--merge              # Merge with existing .claude/
```

## Implementation Steps

1. Create package directory structure
2. Write CLI script (bin/cli.js)
3. Copy template files
4. Create package.json
5. Write README with examples
6. Test locally with `npm link`
7. Publish to npm

